 \includegraphics[width=12cm, height=11cm]{..//figure/dvrgraphic.pdf} 
 \caption{Differences in spring phenology and false spring risk across two species: \textit{Ilex mucronata} (L.) and \textit{Betula alleghaniensis} (Marsh.). We mapped a hypothetical false spring event based on historical weather data and long-term observational phenological data collected at Harvard Forest (O'Keefe, 2014). In this scenario, \textit{Ilex mucronata}, which bursts bud early and generally has a short period between budburst (squares) and leafout (triangles), would be exposed to a false spring event during its duration of vegetative risk (i.e., from budburst to leafout), whereas \textit{Betula alleghaniensis} would avoid it entirely (even though it has a longer duration of vegetative risk), due to later budburst. } \label{fig:region}  
 \end{center}
